Australia's Foreign Minister Julie Bishop wore a headscarf during her visit to Iran . 
  She is the highest-ranking official to visit the country in 12 years . 
  Bishop defended her choice to wear a scarf during a meeting with the Iranian president . 
  She said she did so out of respect for the culture . 
  Opposition Leader Bill Shorten said it was 'ridiculous' to criticise her for wearing a scarf . 
 